Name.repository: University of California, Los Angeles. Library. Performing Arts Special Collections
Title: Hathaway Manuscripts
Summary: Music manuscript fragments used in bindings. Copied in Switzerland, Germany and the Low Countries. Contents from Missal, Gradual, Hymnal, Breviary and Antiphonal.
AltTitle.uniform: Hathaway collection of music manuscript leaves

Rights.servicesContact: UCLA Charles E. Young Research Library Department of Special Collections, A1713 Young Research Library, Box 951575, Los Angeles, CA 90095-1575. E-mail: spec-coll@library.ucla.edu. Phone: (310)825-4989
Name.repository: University of California, Los Angeles. Library. Performing Arts Special Collections
Title: Hathaway 1
Description.note: Breviary: Readings and Responsories.|~|Written in the Alemannic area, presumably in Switzerland.|~|Parchment (rather coarse), 13 long lines; ruling not discernible; pricking in the outer margin.  Written in a late, crude Caroline minuscule with squarish Alemannic features; dark brown ink.  Plain initials in red or stroked with red; initials in the text slashed with yellow; rubrics in red majuscule; neumes of St. Gall type.|~|Used for binding; folio 1 used as a pastedown: the verso is stained and rubbed.|~|ff. 1, 2 and 3 from the same manuscript.

Title: Hathaway 4
AltIdentifier.local: 170/ 768 v.1|~|Hathaway collection of music manuscript leaves
Description.note: Breviary.|~|Parchment, 1 leaf cropped at the top and at the margins.  30 long lines survive; ruling in lead.  Developed Caroline miniscule script; brown ink.  Plain capital initials in red; rubrics in red minuscule; neumes of St. Gall type.|~|Used as pastedown in binding; the verso is rubbed and stained.
